  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Past studies have shown that MRI is useful for staging prostate cancer. This study will use
      magnetic resonance spectroscopic imaging (MRSI) to obtain more information. MRSIs with MRIs
      help doctors locate prostate cancer and determine the extent of tumor before deciding on
      treatment. This study looks at structural and chemical properties of prostates in prostate
      cancer patients before and after treatment.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
